Common Name/Identifiers: just outside of the sanctuary boundary to the west
Site Description/Driver for Monitoring L: This deep water site captures large whale and orca activity offshore and to the west of the TTS in/out of the Strait of Juan de Fuca. It monitors the northwestern area of the sanctuary, including for Naval testing and training activity.

Common Name/Identifiers: in traffic fan approaching San Fran/Oakland
Site Description/Driver for Monitoring L: This low frequency recorder captures sound associated with vessel traffic coming in/out of the Ports of San Francisco and Oakland to the south and west. It's also an area with high baleen whale occurrence seasonally.
